  "body": "Hi, does anyone knows how to get block timestamp in milliseconds, I know that [eth_getblockbyhash](https://eth.wiki/json-rpc/API#eth_getblockbyhash) can get block timestamp but it's in UNIX timestamp second format, I want it's in millisecond because I need more accurate time.\r\n\r\nBtw, since the block timestamp is set by the miner, does all the miner have synced time? is it possible that one miner's time is 5 seconds faster than another, so actually I can't trust the block timestampï¼Ÿ",
