    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The ethereum block header only stores the timestamp in UNIX seconds, so it is not possible to get the timestamp in milliseconds. \r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/76700ac892f6fe3d7865fbe2f724626c72a04227/miner/worker.go#L515\r\n\r\nYes, the miners can set the timestamp arbitrarily (within some window) so you can't trust the timestamp to be accurate. ",
